7. Albani putres: Alba Longa was the head of the Latin league of thirty confederate towns. When conquered by Rome, its leading families, Albani patres, were said to have been transferred to Rome, which now be· came chief of the confederacy. The terrn refers here, in general, to the great senatorial families.
